For the character in l16 between bhūme and fpa, Kielhorn notes that the back of the impression (meaning the back of the paper rubbing, I suppose) shows that this character has been struck out. Kielhorn says it is perhaps e or ca; Mirashi just reads it as an unclear ca and notes that it is superfluous, not mentioning the erasure. It could also be va (which it resembles more than ca) or even da. 
--><!-- 
Kielhorn notes that one would expect bhūmayaḥ/bhūmīnāṁ pañcaviṁśatiḥ and ṣaṣṭiḥ in l16-17. Mirashi does not emend the text. 
--><!-- 
The break of l18-19 seems to have been engraved originally as vitarāmaḥ / tad. The visarga was deleted, as noted by both Kielhorn and Mirashi. (It is not visible in the rubbing at all as printed in Shastri; there are what may be traces of it in the reproduction in EI03.) After deleting the visarga, sta was engraved at the end of l18, and this character extends beyond the margin of l17 and 19. At the beginning of l19, ta does not appear to have been cancelled. 
--><!-- 
Mirashi prints lavaṇa and kkeṇi in l20; the plate has na and kkre. 
--><!-- 
The visarga preceding the hole in l23 seems to have a punctuation dash between the dots, but neither Kielhorn nor Mirashi note this so I assume it is a random scratch. 
--></p>
